Don't emit ``bad-format-string`` / ``bad-format-character`` against f-strings
and ``.format()`` calls when any argument has a custom ``__format__``. Custom
``__format__`` methods (e.g. ``astropy.units.Quantity`` accepting ``"cds"`` or
``"latex"``) consume arbitrary spec text that the standard mini-format-spec
parser doesn't understand.

Refs #11041
